The new code refactors the module into aws_providers and aws_models and allows extending to new models.
Supported aws providers - Bedrock and Sagemaker
Supported models - Mistral, Anthropic, Llama (extensible design to add custom models)

```
"""Test harness: Testing the AWS modules"""
import dspy
from dspy import AWSAnthropic, AWSLlama2, AWSMistral, AWSModel, Bedrock, Sagemaker


class QASignature(dspy.Signature):
    """answer the question"""

    question = dspy.InputField()
    answer = dspy.OutputField()


def test_aws_models(lm: AWSModel):
    """Test the models on the given AWS provider"""

    predict_func = dspy.ChainOfThought(QASignature)
    with dspy.context(lm=lm):
        answer = predict_func(question="What is the capital of France")
        assert "paris" in str(answer).lower()
        print(answer)


if __name__ == "__main__":
    # NOTE: Configure your AWS credentials with the AWS CLI before running this test!

    bedrock = Bedrock(region_name="us-west-2")
    test_aws_models(AWSMistral(bedrock, model="mistral.mixtral-8x7b-instruct-v0:1"))
    test_aws_models(AWSMistral(bedrock, "mistral.mistral-7b-instruct-v0:2"))
    test_aws_models(AWSAnthropic(bedrock, "anthropic.claude-3-haiku-20240307-v1:0"))
    test_aws_models(AWSAnthropic(bedrock, "anthropic.claude-3-sonnet-20240229-v1:0"))
    # this is slower than molasses and generates irrelevant content after the answer!!
    # You may have to wait for 10-15min before it returns
    test_aws_models(AWSLlama2(bedrock, "meta.llama2-70b-chat-v1"))

    # NOTE: Configure your Sagemaker endpoints before running this test!
    sagemaker = Sagemaker(region_name="us-west-2")
    # NOTE: Replace model value below with your own endpoint name
    test_aws_models(AWSMistral(sagemaker, model="g5-48xlarge-mixtral-8x7b"))

'body': 'in `dsp.modules.HFClientVLLM` class the `kwargs` are supposed to be passed to the vllm openai endpoint (cf. the docs) but are discarded instead. This is related to the issue here : https://github.com/stanfordnlp/dspy/issues/718

In this PR, there are some modifications to the `dsp.modules.HFClientVLLM` class:

1.  In the `__init__` the `kwargs` were actually unused. In this PR those are attached to `self.` instead of being discarded.
2. The model of the payload was provided by the `kwargs` of `_generate` method, disregarding the value initialized in the `__init__`. This is fixed in this PR.
3. Two optional parameters were made mandatory (`temperature` and `max_tokens`) in the `_generate` method. Those were made mandatory because it was a direct `kwargs["<parameter>"]`, which would raise `KeyError`. In this PR, those two dictionary access have been deleted.
4. Finally, still in the `_generate` method, the kwargs were never actually passed to the vllm endpoint. In this PR we fix this by unpacking the `kwargs` into the payload so that the extra arguments.', 'reactions': {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/stanfordnlp/dspy/issues/719/reactions', 'total_count': 0, '+1': 0, '-1': 0, 'laugh': 0, 'hooray': 0, 'confused': 0, 'heart': 0, 'rocket': 0, 'eyes': 0}, 'timeline_url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/stanfordnlp/dspy/issues/719/timeline', 'performed_via_github_app': None, 'state_reason': None}, 'comment': {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/stanfordnlp/dspy/issues/comments/2030544433', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/stanfordnlp/dspy/pull/719#issuecomment-2030544433', 'issue_url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/stanfordnlp/dspy/issues/719', 'id': 2030544433, 'node_id': 'IC_kwDOIv2ufM55B6Yx', 'user': {'login': 'arnavsinghvi11', 'id': 54859892, 'node_id': 'MDQ6VXNlcjU0ODU5ODky', 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/54859892?v=4', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/arnavsinghvi11', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/arnavsinghvi11', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/arnavsinghvi11/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/arnavsinghvi11/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/arnavsinghvi11/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/arnavsinghvi11/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/arnavsinghvi11/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/arnavsinghvi11/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/arnavsinghvi11/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/arnavsinghvi11/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/arnavsinghvi11/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}, 'created_at': '2024-04-01T20:58:56Z', 'updated_at': '2024-04-01T20:58:56Z', 'author_association': 'COLLABORATOR', 'body': 'got it! could you also run `ruff check . --fix-only` which is currently failing tests? 'body': 'in `dsp.modules.HFClientVLLM` class the `kwargs` are supposed to be passed to the vllm openai endpoint (cf. the docs) but are discarded instead. This is related to the issue here : https://github.com/stanfordnlp/dspy/issues/718

In this PR, there are some modifications to the `dsp.modules.HFClientVLLM` class:

1.  In the `__init__` the `kwargs` were actually unused. In this PR those are attached to `self.` instead of being discarded.
2. The model of the payload was provided by the `kwargs` of `_generate` method, disregarding the value initialized in the `__init__`. This is fixed in this PR.
3. Two optional parameters were made mandatory (`temperature` and `max_tokens`) in the `_generate` method. Those were made mandatory because it was a direct `kwargs["<parameter>"]`, which would raise `KeyError`. In this PR, those two dictionary access have been deleted.
4. Finally, still in the `_generate` method, the kwargs were never actually passed to the vllm endpoint. In this PR we fix this by unpacking the `kwargs` into the payload so that the extra arguments.', 'reactions': {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/stanfordnlp/dspy/issues/719/reactions', 'total_count': 0, '+1': 0, '-1': 0, 'laugh': 0, 'hooray': 0, 'confused': 0, 'heart': 0, 'rocket': 0, 'eyes': 0}, 'timeline_url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/stanfordnlp/dspy/issues/719/timeline', 'performed_via_github_app': None, 'state_reason': None}, 'comment': {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/stanfordnlp/dspy/issues/comments/2030470163', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/stanfordnlp/dspy/pull/719#issuecomment-2030470163', 'issue_url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/stanfordnlp/dspy/issues/719', 'id': 2030470163, 'node_id': 'IC_kwDOIv2ufM55BoQT', 'user': {'login': 'remiconnesson', 'id': 28846642, 'node_id': 'MDQ6VXNlcjI4ODQ2NjQy', 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/28846642?v=4', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/remiconnesson', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/remiconnesson', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/remiconnesson/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/remiconnesson/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/remiconnesson/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/remiconnesson/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/remiconnesson/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/remiconnesson/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/remiconnesson/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/remiconnesson/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/remiconnesson/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}, 'created_at': '2024-04-01T20:06:15Z', 'updated_at': '2024-04-01T20:06:15Z', 'author_association': 'NONE', 'body': 'https://docs.vllm.ai/en/latest/serving/openai_compatible_server.html#extra-parameters-for-completions-api
